NX,0.20384615384615384,"The results in Theorem 3 broadens the applicability of an effective BER estimator to a larger class of
datasets, e.g., to scenarios where the dataset includes multiple data samples representing the same
feature. For example, ÏˆDN works well on a noisy dataset where each data sample has multiple labels.
Moreover, as we will see in Section 4.2, ÏˆDN is also useful for one-hot labels. We also expect that
ÏˆDN will work well with privatized datasets where noise was added to enhance privacy [26]."
